3
00:01:46,850 --> 00:01:49,750
All right, everyone, let's start the class.

4
00:01:49,750 --> 00:01:53,090
Today, we're learning about
the history of Wano!

5
00:01:53,090 --> 00:01:54,720
– Yes, ma'am!
– Yes, ma'am!

6
00:02:01,470 --> 00:02:02,810
Now, everyone...

7
00:02:04,310 --> 00:02:07,380
Does anyone know what a closed nation is?

8
00:02:07,380 --> 00:02:08,810
I know!

9
00:02:08,810 --> 00:02:12,940
It's a country that shuts its
entrances to maintain peace!

10
00:02:12,940 --> 00:02:14,070
That's correct!

11
00:02:14,070 --> 00:02:15,770
Easy peasy!

12
00:02:16,270 --> 00:02:16,990
Next...

13
00:02:16,990 --> 00:02:19,960
What is an open nation?

14
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:20,480
Me!

15
00:02:20,480 --> 00:02:21,090
Here!

16
00:02:21,090 --> 00:02:22,910
Pick me!

17
00:02:21,090 --> 00:02:22,910
Me, me!

18
00:02:22,910 --> 00:02:24,160
You there.

19
00:02:24,160 --> 00:02:25,230
Yes.

20
00:02:25,230 --> 00:02:30,290
It's a nation that welcomes
evil foreigners and ideas. It's terrible!

21
00:02:31,910 --> 00:02:36,380
All foreign countries want
something from Wano!

22
00:02:36,380 --> 00:02:39,050
That's exactly correct!

23
00:02:40,130 --> 00:02:41,800
A long time ago...

24
00:02:42,890 --> 00:02:46,990
there were some fools who
tried to open Wano.

25
00:02:49,520 --> 00:02:53,440
– Oden and the Nine Red Scabbards!
– Oden and the Nine Red Scabbards!

26
00:02:53,440 --> 00:02:57,370
Oh, I didn't say you could answer that.

27
00:02:57,370 --> 00:02:59,400
Wiggle, wiggle, wiggle, wiggle!

28
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:02,770
– There it is! Her stretchy neck!
– There it is! Her stretchy neck!

29
00:03:02,770 --> 00:03:05,780
You naughty kids answered
without my permission!

30
00:03:05,780 --> 00:03:08,080
Why can't we answer?

31
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:11,620
Because the Nine Red Scabbards...

32
00:03:11,620 --> 00:03:15,520
is a name I'd rather not hear.

33
00:03:16,650 --> 00:03:20,460
But it's been two decades now.

34
00:03:24,090 --> 00:03:29,930
There was a hero that defeated
those evil samurai.

35
00:03:31,310 --> 00:03:34,610
– It was Shogun Kurozumi Orochi!
– It was Shogun Kurozumi Orochi!

36
00:03:34,610 --> 00:03:36,280
That's correct!

37
00:03:36,280 --> 00:03:38,180
Orochi Two-Sword Style!

38
00:03:38,180 --> 00:03:42,320
Watch out, Red Scabbards!
I'm gonna bring you to justice!

39
00:03:45,930 --> 00:03:48,760
What a shameful education.

40
00:03:48,760 --> 00:03:51,830
It's all lies!

41
00:03:51,830 --> 00:03:56,670
Shogun Orochi saved Wano
from the bad guys!

42
00:03:56,670 --> 00:03:58,280
That's right.

43
00:03:58,890 --> 00:04:00,050
Twenty years ago...

44
00:04:01,220 --> 00:04:03,930
all of those bad people died.

45
00:04:03,930 --> 00:04:07,010
And Wano became...

46
00:04:07,010 --> 00:04:10,810
the peaceful country it is today!

47
00:04:15,780 --> 00:04:19,070
Shogun Orochi is a coward!

48
00:04:19,070 --> 00:04:23,050
B-B-Boss Kyoshiro! What are you saying?!

49
00:04:23,050 --> 00:04:24,990
You're too loud!

50
00:04:25,450 --> 00:04:28,780
Shut up, you idiot!

51
00:04:31,410 --> 00:04:32,660
Don't be a wimp!

52
00:04:32,660 --> 00:04:37,030
Who cares if anyone hears me? It's the truth.

53
00:04:52,890 --> 00:04:56,300
Sake! Bring me more sake!

54
00:04:59,570 --> 00:05:02,400
Does he have ties to Orochi?

55
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:04,110
Napping Kyoshiro...

56
00:05:04,110 --> 00:05:07,950
Maybe I can glean some useful information.

57
00:05:09,670 --> 00:05:11,370
Twenty years ago...

58
00:05:11,370 --> 00:05:13,880
before she died,

59
00:05:13,880 --> 00:05:17,710
Oden's wife uttered these words
as their castle burned around her:

60
00:05:29,220 --> 00:05:32,640
"You are the moon, unaware
of the approach of daybreak.

61
00:05:32,640 --> 00:05:36,230
May your purpose be fulfilled...

62
00:05:36,230 --> 00:05:41,980
and case nine shadows on
the night woven of twenty years.

63
00:05:41,980 --> 00:05:45,880
Then you shall know the brilliance of dawn!"

64
00:05:54,250 --> 00:05:59,630
She likely said it out of desperation,
but Shogun Orochi didn't take it that way!

65
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:11,470
How did he take it?

66
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:16,180
Shogun Orochi...

67
00:06:16,180 --> 00:06:17,920
Go on!

68
00:06:27,130 --> 00:06:29,230
How did he take it?!

69
00:06:30,470 --> 00:06:33,200
Oh, right. Like this.

70
00:06:35,490 --> 00:06:38,120
"A curse upon you!"

71
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:39,670
Like a ghost?!

72
00:06:39,670 --> 00:06:44,590
"To settle a grudge, the ghosts
of nine samurai will appear...

73
00:06:46,300 --> 00:06:50,060
on a moonlit night twenty years from now...

74
00:06:50,060 --> 00:06:51,220
to kill you."

75
00:06:51,220 --> 00:06:54,100
Meaning "to kill Shogun Orochi"!

76
00:06:55,220 --> 00:06:58,480
"They'll open Wano to the world"!

77
00:06:59,440 --> 00:07:03,030
And now, twenty years have passed!

78
00:07:05,650 --> 00:07:09,490
That's why Shogun Orochi is afraid!

79
00:07:09,490 --> 00:07:15,630
He actually believes that the ghosts of
the Kozuki clan are coming to kill him!

80
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:20,660
I would love to fight them!

81
00:07:25,420 --> 00:07:27,460
But then, what can the dead do?

82
00:07:31,890 --> 00:07:34,970
The samurai of the Kozuki Clan...

83
00:07:34,970 --> 00:07:39,730
Twenty years ago, we cornered
them in the castle...

84
00:07:42,020 --> 00:07:46,110
and burned them all alive!

85
00:07:56,780 --> 00:08:00,770
Oden Castle once stood here.

86
00:08:01,080 --> 00:08:03,600
But that was just a nickname.

87
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:06,350
It was actually called Kuri Castle!

88
00:08:06,350 --> 00:08:11,220
Since the people of Kuri adored Lord Oden,
they nicknamed the castle after him.

89
00:08:11,220 --> 00:08:12,630
Momo's dad, right?!

90
00:08:12,630 --> 00:08:14,260
That is correct!

91
00:08:14,780 --> 00:08:19,170
Lord Oden was in fact a very brash individual.

92
00:08:19,980 --> 00:08:26,620
He was the son of the venerable Kozuki
Sukiyaki, the former shogun of Wano,

93
00:08:26,620 --> 00:08:30,430
but he was free-spirited and hot-blooded.

94
00:08:38,870 --> 00:08:40,990
He caused so many violent incidents...

95
00:08:40,990 --> 00:08:45,710
that he was eventually banished
from the Flower Capital.

96
00:08:45,710 --> 00:08:46,600
– What?!
– What?!

97
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:47,580
Banished?!

98
00:08:48,450 --> 00:08:51,170
Well, for the young Lord Oden,

99
00:08:51,170 --> 00:08:55,230
the Flower Capital was
too small and too boring.

100
00:09:02,650 --> 00:09:03,770
Damn you!

101
00:09:03,770 --> 00:09:04,810
Go to hell!

102
00:09:07,770 --> 00:09:12,600
At that time, there was a so-called
"lawless area" in Wano.

103
00:09:14,440 --> 00:09:20,280
There, criminals and ronin who had been exiled
from their hometowns banded together.

104
00:09:20,280 --> 00:09:24,410
They would steal from and kill each other.
Every day was a blood bath.

105
00:09:24,410 --> 00:09:28,580
The place was so wild,
even the shogun gave up on it.

106
00:09:28,580 --> 00:09:30,880
That place was Kuri.

107
00:09:33,920 --> 00:09:36,090
How interesting!

108
00:09:38,050 --> 00:09:43,180
Of all the places the young Lord Oden could
wander into it, it was the infamous Kuri!

109
00:09:43,180 --> 00:09:49,520
Then, the most dangerous man in Kuri
approached him with the region's ruffians.

110
00:09:55,740 --> 00:09:58,860
His name was Ashura Doji,
and they clashed immediately!

111
00:10:42,310 --> 00:10:45,160
He skillfully bested Ashura Doji.

112
00:10:46,220 --> 00:10:47,160
And then...

113
00:10:48,410 --> 00:10:52,210
he became the leader of those ruffians.

114
00:10:56,550 --> 00:10:58,780
Oh, he was quite something.

115
00:10:58,780 --> 00:11:00,630
He saved Kuri!

116
00:11:00,630 --> 00:11:05,010
Furthermore, Lord Oden brought
about change to the town!

117
00:11:07,650 --> 00:11:12,010
He started by teaching the ruffians to work.

118
00:11:14,760 --> 00:11:18,570
He developed the town... built the castle...

119
00:11:19,130 --> 00:11:22,830
and created Halcyon Farm for the people.

120
00:11:26,470 --> 00:11:31,080
Kuri became a free and
vibrant region full of laughter.

121
00:11:32,180 --> 00:11:36,130
Ultimately, Shogun Sukiyaki decided...

122
00:11:36,130 --> 00:11:39,590
to bestow Lord Oden with
the title of daimyo of Kuri.

123
00:11:40,670 --> 00:11:46,030
Lord Oden was able to accomplish
all that by the age of twenty.

124
00:11:49,600 --> 00:11:51,890
He dug out a river...

125
00:11:51,890 --> 00:11:53,480
and built docks.

126
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:55,360
He connected regions...

127
00:11:55,360 --> 00:11:57,370
and people.

128
00:12:00,860 --> 00:12:02,390
And then, I...

129
00:12:04,700 --> 00:12:06,620
Right. And...

130
00:12:11,490 --> 00:12:14,260
The people of Kuri truly loved their daimyo.

131
00:12:14,960 --> 00:12:18,960
But Lord Oden remained a free spirit.

132
00:12:19,780 --> 00:12:23,840
Having a great many retainers
didn't suit his style.

133
00:12:28,760 --> 00:12:31,480
He was always saying:

134
00:12:44,730 --> 00:12:49,370
I detest these confines!

135
00:12:59,850 --> 00:13:04,060
Wano was a little too cramped for Lord Oden.

136
00:13:07,510 --> 00:13:09,610
It really takes me back...

137
00:13:11,200 --> 00:13:14,000
It was on this very beach!

138
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:18,770
When we washed ashore here,
everyone called us "the talking dog and cat."

139
00:13:19,310 --> 00:13:22,650
They were afraid of us.

140
00:13:23,490 --> 00:13:25,830
But Lord Oden was different!

141
00:13:28,600 --> 00:13:31,330
What did they do to you?!

142
00:13:31,330 --> 00:13:35,060
It is sheer stupidity to fear
those who are different!

143
00:13:40,360 --> 00:13:42,920
We owe him so much!

144
00:13:44,380 --> 00:13:47,050
He was the Wano samurai...

145
00:13:47,050 --> 00:13:51,220
who fascinated Whitebeard
and earned Roger's respect!

146
00:13:52,820 --> 00:13:55,330
He was a true hero!

147
00:13:55,330 --> 00:13:58,230
He was our lord!

148
00:14:22,820 --> 00:14:25,380
Everyone loved Lord Oden...

149
00:14:35,420 --> 00:14:37,640
Hey! What happened to Oden next?!

150
00:14:39,870 --> 00:14:45,610
He died as a criminal at the Flower Capital!

151
00:14:48,150 --> 00:14:49,700
What?!

152
00:14:52,820 --> 00:14:55,040
You've gotta be kidding!

153
00:14:55,040 --> 00:14:57,580
That dirty snake! Orochi!

154
00:14:58,790 --> 00:15:00,830
I can't believe it!

155
00:15:02,330 --> 00:15:03,630
That's awful!

156
00:15:03,630 --> 00:15:07,030
The horrific death of Lord Oden...

157
00:15:07,650 --> 00:15:10,570
might have happened twenty years ago...

158
00:15:11,050 --> 00:15:13,810
but for us...

159
00:15:13,810 --> 00:15:16,610
it was only a few months ago...!

160
00:15:17,670 --> 00:15:21,680
Kozuki Oden was a brave samurai...!

161
00:15:22,820 --> 00:15:24,610
His final moment...

162
00:15:24,980 --> 00:15:29,820
still vividly replays in my memory!

163
00:15:33,910 --> 00:15:36,530
What a hero!

164
00:15:40,090 --> 00:15:44,090
It's a wonder the rest of you made it out alive.

165
00:15:44,090 --> 00:15:45,390
Indeed...

166
00:15:45,390 --> 00:15:48,280
We no longer had allies,

167
00:15:48,280 --> 00:15:52,470
so from there, we just ran for our lives!

168
00:15:53,730 --> 00:15:55,720
We fled the execution grounds...

169
00:15:55,720 --> 00:15:58,640
and ran straight to Oden Castle!

170
00:16:03,230 --> 00:16:07,020
Along the way, Inuarashi
and Nekomamushi began to squabble,

171
00:16:07,020 --> 00:16:11,320
and were caught by Orochi's underlings,
so we left them for dead!

172
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:14,780
We knew that no matter what
happened to any of us,

173
00:16:14,780 --> 00:16:17,740
someone had to reach Oden Castle!

174
00:16:18,450 --> 00:16:22,410
Orochi intended to bring down
the Kozuki clan by targeting...

175
00:16:24,220 --> 00:16:27,660
Lord Momonosuke, who was at the castle!

176
00:16:36,310 --> 00:16:38,430
Th-The castle...!

177
00:16:39,420 --> 00:16:45,210
But Kaido had already made his move.
The castle was ablaze.

178
00:16:48,480 --> 00:16:51,740
You damn bastards!

179
00:16:51,740 --> 00:16:54,150
I'll never forgive you!

180
00:16:55,070 --> 00:16:57,240
Get them!

181
00:17:06,960 --> 00:17:09,130
Flower Shuriken!

182
00:17:14,250 --> 00:17:18,760
Lord Momonosuke,
his younger sister Hiyori...

183
00:17:18,760 --> 00:17:23,350
and their mother, the Lady Kozuki Toki,
were still inside the castle.

184
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:25,680
Mother...

185
00:17:30,760 --> 00:17:33,440
Lord Momonosuke! Lady Hiyori!

186
00:17:33,440 --> 00:17:34,990
Lady Toki!

187
00:17:37,530 --> 00:17:39,820
Come on! Hurry up!

188
00:17:50,220 --> 00:17:52,500
Lord Momonosuke!

189
00:17:52,500 --> 00:17:54,710
I'm so glad you're okay!

190
00:17:55,330 --> 00:17:57,770
Lady Hiyori! Lady Toki!

191
00:18:03,470 --> 00:18:05,710
I'm sorry!

192
00:18:05,710 --> 00:18:09,600
Though we were there,
we allowed Lord Oden to be...

193
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:12,860
It was not your fault.

194
00:18:12,860 --> 00:18:13,800
But...

195
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:15,660
Raise your heads.

196
00:18:16,580 --> 00:18:19,820
Lady Toki, it's dangerous here! We must leave!

197
00:18:21,250 --> 00:18:23,160
I am staying.

198
00:18:24,490 --> 00:18:25,690
You cannot!

199
00:18:25,690 --> 00:18:28,480
Let's get out of here!

200
00:18:28,480 --> 00:18:29,720
Lady Toki!

201
00:18:32,780 --> 00:18:36,460
Then we will stay and share
the same fate as you!

202
00:18:37,270 --> 00:18:39,970
You must escape... to the future.

203
00:18:40,930 --> 00:18:42,260
The future?

204
00:18:42,260 --> 00:18:46,090
Travel to the past is impossible...

205
00:18:46,090 --> 00:18:48,230
but one can leap ahead to the future.

206
00:18:51,180 --> 00:18:54,670
I traveled farther and farther into the future...

207
00:18:54,670 --> 00:18:58,270
thanks to the mysterious Time-Time Fruit...

208
00:18:58,270 --> 00:19:03,740
until arriving here where my journey will end.

209
00:19:03,740 --> 00:19:06,860
It was hard to believe...

210
00:19:06,860 --> 00:19:11,790
but rumor had it that Lady Toki
was born in the distant past.

211
00:19:13,760 --> 00:19:15,010
You mean...

212
00:19:15,800 --> 00:19:17,960
you met Lord Oden.

213
00:19:17,960 --> 00:19:21,890
Yes. That is why I will stay here.

214
00:19:28,020 --> 00:19:29,520
Who could ever stop...

215
00:19:30,490 --> 00:19:32,700
such conviction?

216
00:19:43,380 --> 00:19:47,290
If we really are able to leap into the future...

217
00:19:49,330 --> 00:19:54,170
We will surely fulfill Lord Oden's dream

218
00:19:54,170 --> 00:19:57,920
and take down Orochi and Kaido!

219
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:05,460
And we will definitely...

220
00:20:05,460 --> 00:20:07,850
open this country!

221
00:20:11,180 --> 00:20:14,650
Please look after Momonosuke.

222
00:20:16,070 --> 00:20:17,190
Mother?

223
00:20:20,870 --> 00:20:25,160
No, I don't want that! I will stay here with you!

224
00:20:25,160 --> 00:20:28,580
Mother, please don't do this!

225
00:20:28,580 --> 00:20:33,790
Mother! Mother!

226
00:20:50,760 --> 00:20:52,790
Ouch...

227
00:20:57,900 --> 00:21:00,350
Huh?! What the...?!

228
00:21:04,900 --> 00:21:08,460
Is this a dream?! Where are we?!

229
00:21:08,460 --> 00:21:10,900
Where is the castle?! And the fire?!

230
00:21:10,900 --> 00:21:13,830
Lady Toki! Lady Hiyori!

231
00:21:16,650 --> 00:21:21,260
Where are you, Mother?!

232
00:21:21,930 --> 00:21:24,470
Please wait, Lord Momonosuke!

233
00:21:24,470 --> 00:21:26,840
Mother!

234
00:21:29,930 --> 00:21:31,590
Kin'emon!

235
00:21:39,560 --> 00:21:42,610
Are these our graves?!

236
00:21:42,610 --> 00:21:45,100
They're so old!

237
00:21:45,710 --> 00:21:47,870
It was real...

238
00:21:47,870 --> 00:21:49,570
Lady Toki's power was real!

239
00:21:56,490 --> 00:21:59,350
Then that is the town in Kuri?

240
00:22:02,490 --> 00:22:05,950
This is... the Wano of the future?!

241
00:22:09,110 --> 00:22:12,210
Since we came from the past...

242
00:22:12,800 --> 00:22:17,500
the world had become alien
to us after twenty years.

243
00:22:18,070 --> 00:22:19,940
We decided to walk about...

244
00:22:19,940 --> 00:22:24,180
and gather information on
how Orochi's influence...

245
00:22:24,180 --> 00:22:25,860
had corrupted this land.

246
00:22:26,730 --> 00:22:28,850
We saw a row of factories...

247
00:22:28,850 --> 00:22:31,780
and a great many smokestacks
blackening the sky.

248
00:22:31,780 --> 00:22:36,620
Undrinkable water...
Food under strict control...

249
00:22:37,250 --> 00:22:40,480
Many daimyo ousted and regions destroyed!

250
00:22:40,480 --> 00:22:42,090
The land was barren!

251
00:22:42,090 --> 00:22:46,880
Even the Kozuki name was poisoned
because of their lies.

252
00:22:47,800 --> 00:22:52,030
This land was no longer...

253
00:22:52,710 --> 00:22:55,260
the Wano we once knew!

254
00:22:59,910 --> 00:23:03,690
I thought no one would would
take up arms together with us.

255
00:23:18,330 --> 00:23:19,370
Unbelievable...

256
00:23:22,330 --> 00:23:26,270
You're Lord Kozuki Momonosuke...

257
00:23:26,270 --> 00:23:28,840
aren't you?

258
00:23:33,470 --> 00:23:37,270
You look just like you did twenty years ago...!

259
00:23:37,960 --> 00:23:42,460
Lady Toki's last words were true!

260
00:23:47,820 --> 00:23:53,950
I was once a retainer from Kibi.
My name is Jibuemon!

261
00:23:53,950 --> 00:23:56,010
For twenty years...

262
00:23:56,850 --> 00:24:00,260
I've been waiting for you.

263
00:24:00,260 --> 00:24:04,680
We had faith in the words
of your mother, Lady Toki...

264
00:24:05,290 --> 00:24:07,120
and we waited for this day!

265
00:24:10,550 --> 00:24:14,810
Mother's... last words...

266
00:24:15,360 --> 00:24:16,790
Tell me what she said!

267
00:24:16,790 --> 00:24:18,110
Of course!

268
00:24:18,110 --> 00:24:19,860
This is what she said.

269
00:24:22,330 --> 00:24:26,060
"You are the moon, unaware
of the approach of daybreak.

270
00:24:26,060 --> 00:24:29,360
May your purpose be fulfilled...

271
00:24:29,360 --> 00:24:35,110
and cast nine shadows
on the night woven of twenty years.

272
00:24:35,110 --> 00:24:38,740
Then you shall know the brilliance of dawn!"

273
00:24:39,800 --> 00:24:42,460
Lady Toki's last words seemed to predict...

274
00:24:42,460 --> 00:24:46,960
that the Kozuki Clan would get
revenge in twenty years.

275
00:24:46,960 --> 00:24:50,550
We thought that it was impossible.

276
00:24:50,550 --> 00:24:58,080
However, we kept our faith because
none of the Red Scabbard's bodies...

277
00:24:58,080 --> 00:25:00,920
were ever found.

278
00:25:04,440 --> 00:25:06,730
Mother...

279
00:25:06,730 --> 00:25:14,050
On the slim chance that you would
actually return in twenty years...

280
00:25:14,050 --> 00:25:18,160
to lead us to victory against Orochi...

281
00:25:18,160 --> 00:25:22,080
we have prepared for the battle ahead.

282
00:25:22,080 --> 00:25:24,870
There are people who intend to fight...

283
00:25:24,870 --> 00:25:29,130
regardless of where they are
or what they're doing.

284
00:25:32,380 --> 00:25:36,680
They await your orders,
marked by a moon on their ankles!

285
00:25:43,850 --> 00:25:45,920
Wh... What?!

286
00:25:46,600 --> 00:25:49,810
You mean that after twenty years,
we still have allies?!

287
00:25:49,810 --> 00:25:52,570
How many men are there?!

288
00:25:52,570 --> 00:25:55,250
We can't be sure...

289
00:25:55,250 --> 00:26:01,160
However, people all over Wano
have been waiting for this opportunity!

290
00:26:02,780 --> 00:26:04,250
To take down Kaido...

291
00:26:04,860 --> 00:26:09,080
we need to have as many allies as possible.

292
00:26:09,600 --> 00:26:14,300
Could you go and recruit
like-minded people throughout Wano?

293
00:26:14,850 --> 00:26:19,760
But you must do so... from the shadows.

294
00:26:19,760 --> 00:26:21,270
Yes, sir!

295
00:26:21,270 --> 00:26:23,390
We will devote ourselves to our task!

296
00:26:23,850 --> 00:26:29,790
The thought that Wano might still
have a future kept our hope alive.

297
00:26:29,790 --> 00:26:33,190
We had Kiku keep an eye on our enemies...

298
00:26:33,890 --> 00:26:38,820
while Kanjuro, Raizo,
Lord Momonosuke, and I...

299
00:26:38,820 --> 00:26:42,750
set out on our journey to recruit allies.

300
00:26:43,280 --> 00:26:46,500
The mere act of leaving
this country is a crime.

301
00:26:46,500 --> 00:26:51,460
So as soon as someone
spotted us, they gave chase.

302
00:26:51,460 --> 00:26:55,170
On top of that, since
none of us knew how to sail...

303
00:26:55,170 --> 00:27:00,230
we tried to reach Zou
but were shipwrecked in no time.

304
00:27:00,230 --> 00:27:03,950
We got separated from Raizo in the chaos!

305
00:27:03,950 --> 00:27:07,220
We'll meet on Zou!

306
00:27:07,220 --> 00:27:09,610
Raizo...!

307
00:27:09,610 --> 00:27:11,560
Raizo...!

308
00:27:11,560 --> 00:27:15,800
We were an inch from death when
we washed ashore at Dressrosa...

309
00:27:15,800 --> 00:27:19,570
but were pursued by Doflamingo,
who was connected to Kaido.

310
00:27:19,570 --> 00:27:24,790
We were separated from Lord Momonosuke,
who mistakenly boarded a strange ship!

311
00:27:27,910 --> 00:27:31,040
Lord Momonosuke!

312
00:27:31,560 --> 00:27:37,490
Then, I got separated from Kanjuro
while following after Lord Momonosuke!

313
00:27:37,490 --> 00:27:40,170
Don't worry about me!

314
00:27:40,170 --> 00:27:43,100
Kanjuro...!

315
00:27:43,100 --> 00:27:45,350
Kanjuro...!

316
00:27:46,330 --> 00:27:52,060
Indeed, we fell apart soon after
leaving the shores of Wano.

317
00:27:56,580 --> 00:28:01,690
Even when arriving at Punk Hazard
in my search for Lord Momonosuke,

318
00:28:01,690 --> 00:28:04,870
Caesar—one of Kaido's puppets—stood in my way.

319
00:28:04,870 --> 00:28:09,290
Not to mention, I was chopped up by Sir Law before we joined forces.

320
00:28:15,050 --> 00:28:16,960
My situation had become dire!

321
00:28:18,020 --> 00:28:20,720
That's when I met all of you!

322
00:28:28,670 --> 00:28:31,020
How cool is that?!

323
00:28:31,020 --> 00:28:32,640
Who are you?

324
00:28:32,640 --> 00:28:35,190
The dragon just talked!

325
00:28:35,190 --> 00:28:38,730
How obscene! All you have is a breast-band!

326
00:28:38,730 --> 00:28:40,680
Oh, you don't like it?

327
00:28:41,190 --> 00:28:42,700
No, I love it!

328
00:28:42,700 --> 00:28:45,710
You can't eat me!

329
00:28:45,710 --> 00:28:48,240
If you try to eat me, I'll eat you first!

330
00:28:48,240 --> 00:28:50,620
Comport yourself!

331
00:28:55,120 --> 00:28:58,970
Looking back, it was crisis after crisis...

332
00:28:59,650 --> 00:29:01,700
but I met good people.

333
00:29:02,380 --> 00:29:07,700
I was able to return with dependable allies
who I can trust with my life.

334
00:29:08,300 --> 00:29:12,140
Orochi's forces may have
mentioned our names before...

335
00:29:12,140 --> 00:29:17,730
but thankfully they do not seem to
truly believe that this is happening!

336
00:29:17,730 --> 00:29:21,820
They consider us to be nothing but ghosts.

337
00:29:21,820 --> 00:29:27,160
That is why we have yet to be
placed on the wanted list.

338
00:29:27,160 --> 00:29:31,550
Even our return to the country
has remained undetected.

339
00:29:31,550 --> 00:29:34,910
I was also unaware of this
despite our common allegiance.

340
00:29:34,910 --> 00:29:37,630
Oh, sorry about that.

341
00:29:37,630 --> 00:29:39,540
Hey, get a room already!

342
00:29:42,980 --> 00:29:47,800
It is essential that we keep our presence
a secret from Kaido's forces...

343
00:29:48,800 --> 00:29:50,390
until it is time to fight.

344
00:29:56,640 --> 00:29:59,270
Alright! I got it!

345
00:29:59,270 --> 00:30:03,900
We are up against huge armies
led by Kaido and Kurozumi Orochi!

346
00:30:03,900 --> 00:30:07,610
On our side, we have...

347
00:30:07,610 --> 00:30:11,580
The Straw Hats, led by Sir Luffy.

348
00:30:11,580 --> 00:30:15,540
The Heart Pirates, led by Sir Law.

349
00:30:15,540 --> 00:30:21,130
The minks, comprised of Inuarashi's
Musketeers and Nekomamushi's Guardians.

350
00:30:21,130 --> 00:30:27,040
And any samurai with
a rebellious mind that we can recruit.

351
00:30:27,040 --> 00:30:31,600
Ideally, we'll have around
five thousand people!

352
00:30:31,600 --> 00:30:35,750
However, we are not looking
to wage an all out war.

353
00:30:37,020 --> 00:30:42,440
We'll want to covertly gather intelligence on
our enemies, such as Kaido, and devise a plan...

354
00:30:46,610 --> 00:30:49,030
to take the heads...

355
00:30:50,070 --> 00:30:51,450
of their leaders!

356
00:01:45,450 --> 00:01:49,750
Flower Capital

357
00:02:16,990 --> 00:02:19,950
"Kurozumi Orochi"

358
00:02:46,140 --> 00:02:49,520
Kozuki Oden

359
00:04:36,960 --> 00:04:39,670
The Korozumi Clan's Money Changer

360
00:04:39,710 --> 00:04:43,130
"Napping" Kyoshiro

361
00:13:06,050 --> 00:13:10,680
Daytime Duke Inuarashi
Mokomo Dukedom

362
00:14:16,540 --> 00:14:25,380
Kozuki Oden
